{"cursor":"2772","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n{{Infobox person\n| name = Paul Germain image = birthname = birth_date = birth_place = Los\n| Angeles, California othername = occupation = Animation Writer, Television\n| Producer, Director, Production Staff, Voice Director years_active =\n| 1983âpresent spouse = Beatrice Mills Germain (August 13, 1988âpresent; 3\n| children) website =\n}} 'Paul Germain' (born June 6, 1959) is an American animation screenwriter and\nproducer. Among the shows Germain has written and/or produced for are\n[[Rugrats]],[[All Grown Up!]], [[The Simpsons]], [[Recess (TV series)|Recess]],\n[[Even Stevens]], [[Lloyd in Space]], [[The Tracey Ullman Show]], and\n[[Beethoven (TV series)|Beethoven: The Animated Series]]. Germain was one of the\ncreators of, and the primary creative force behind, the award-winning Rugrats.\nWith his Rugrats colleague Joe Ansolabehere, he is the creator of Recess, and\nco-developer of Safety King and [[Lloyd in Space]]. Germain was born in Los\nAngeles, California.\n\nAmong his film credits are [[Say Anything...]], [[Big (film)|Big]] and\n[[Broadcast News (film)|Broadcast News]].\n\nGermain's eldest son Tom was the inspiration for the Rugrats character Tommy\nPickles. The school in Recess shares the name of Third Street School, an actual\nschool in Los Angeles where all of his children went. Mikey, a character in\nRecess, shares his youngest son's name. His wife's childhood photos were the\nmodel for Gretchen Grundler, also from Recess. His daughter, Helen Rose, was the\ninspiration for Lloyd's younger sister.\n\nPaul youngest brother is Marc \"Mr K\" Germain, a popular talk-show host in Los\nAngeles and formerly known as Mr. KABC and before that as \"Mr. KFI\".\n\nHe has recently been credited as screenwriter on [[Tinker Bell and the Great\nFairy Rescue]].\n\nGermain is currently working as voice director on [[Pound Puppies (2010 TV\nseries)|Pound Puppies]].\n","linknr":122,"url":"Paul_Ge